    <FaqItem
      question="What is the most effective lead generation method for local businesses?"
      answer="Google Business Profile optimisation produces the highest return on time investment for most local businesses — it is free, targets high-intent searchers at exactly the right moment, and improvements compound over time as reviews and content accumulate. For fastest results, paid options (Google Local Service Ads, Facebook Local Ads) deliver leads within days. For long-term compounding returns, local SEO and a systematic review generation programme deliver the best cost-per-lead over time."
    />
    <FaqItem
      question="How do I generate leads for a local business with no budget?"
      answer="The three best zero-budget methods: (1) Optimise your Google Business Profile completely — add photos, respond to all reviews, post weekly updates. (2) Join and participate actively in local Facebook groups — provide genuine value and build community visibility. (3) Build a referral programme — ask satisfied customers for referrals and reviews immediately after a positive service interaction. These three approaches alone generate consistent local leads at zero cost."
    />
    <FaqItem
      question="Does local SEO still work in 2026?"
      answer="Yes. Local SEO remains one of the highest-ROI investments for service-area businesses. The local pack (map and three listings at the top of local search results) captures a significant share of clicks for high-intent location searches. Key ranking factors are Google Business Profile completeness, review quantity and recency, website relevance signals, and citation consistency. AI-generated search summaries have changed some aspects of organic search, but local pack results remain a distinct and valuable traffic source."
    />
    <FaqItem
      question="How important are online reviews for local business lead generation?"
      answer="Reviews are critical on two levels. First, consumer behaviour: the majority of people read reviews before choosing a local service provider. Second, algorithm: Google reviews are a direct ranking factor in local search — more recent, higher-rated reviews consistently produce better rankings. A systematic approach to requesting reviews from satisfied customers immediately after service is one of the highest-ROI marketing activities available to any local business."
    />
    <FaqItem
      question="What is the difference between local and national lead generation?"
      answer="Local lead generation operates within a defined geographic area and relies on proximity signals, community reputation, and location-specific targeting. National lead generation targets unlimited geographic scope using different channels. The underlying skills — email marketing, landing pages, paid social, follow-up automation — are the same in both contexts. A local business owner who develops digital marketing skills can apply them to grow both their local presence and, if they choose, an online income stream alongside it."
